plugin: manual
name: input/mouse
requires: device.category == 'MOUSE'
_description:
 This test verifies that your mouse works properly (for basic mouse operations)
  1.- Move the mouse and confirm that the pointer moves around the screen.
  2.- Right click on a window or the desktop and verify that a menu opens.
  3.- Left click on the desktop and then this window and verify that this window has focus.
 .
 Is your mouse working properly?

plugin: manual
name: input/keyboard
command: keyboard_test
requires: device.category == 'KEYBOARD'
_description:
 This test verifies that your keyboard works. Select test and then type some in the text box that opens.
 .
 Is your keyboard working properly?
